      {
        "id": "ec7a3a372585655497e9c63c4805560160af5f67",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 12:24:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> I think Pam mentioned that master has some issues.. \n> Although, I just remembered that Sonar jobs track only master :(\n> Unless we are planning for tech teams repos master branch to point to this future release from elalto oparent\n\nYeah we only run sonar on master branch - because if you run for multiple branches they overwrite the results. Last run wins - so probably don't need this for elalto branch.\n\nNo issues with master since it is a SNAPSHOT that very few projects are pointing to. Its being upgraded to support JDK 11, so there *may* be issues with some plugins needing to be upgraded. But I don't think so for sonar plugin. I think you are safe.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
